title: Prep Roundup: Lewis, Jenkins lead Shiloh Hills victory
text: Prep Roundup: Lewis, Jenkins lead Shiloh Hills victory by MDJ staff reports The Marietta Daily Journal October 26, 2015 01:23 AM | 194 views | 0 | 1 | | Shane Lewis and Jonny Jenkins combined for five touchdowns Friday as Shiloh Hills Christian beat Covenant Christian 54-42 in its first region game.Lewis carried the ball 16 times for 103 yards and three touchdowns, while Jenkins had 18 carries for 224 yards and two scores.Nathan Shipley and Jordan Ratliff added receiving touchdowns, while Lewis also bolstered the defense with 29 tackles. Chase Blount had 18 tackles.Shiloh Hills (4-4, 1-0) will host Peachtree Academy on Friday. Share This Article | similar stories
